{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847761612,"sessionID":"ses_28739d782ffesMLvrTsRXAlpsf","part":{"id":"prt_d78c6625c001X0mL1r2XWLpb3U","messageID":"msg_d78c64252001zYCgDHqNC1DMkv","sessionID":"ses_28739d782ffesMLvrTsRXAlpsf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6151334b83e642ba81aa31b2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/agentd`, `cmd/agentd`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `idle-cleanup/spec.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Reconciler watches Sandbox CR\n13: \n14: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API group `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`. The reconciler SHALL be triggered on Sandbox create and update events via `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).Complete(r)`.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Sandbox creation triggers reconcile\n17: \n18: - **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n19: - **WHEN** a new `Sandbox` object is created in the cluster\n20: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object's namespace and name\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Sandbox update triggers reconcile\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n25: - **WHEN** an existing `Sandbox` object is updated (including annotation changes)\n26: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object's namespace and name\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n31: - **WHEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n32: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked and returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n33: \n34: ### Requirement: Reconciler data structures\n35: \n36: The system SHALL define the following types in `pkg/agentd`:\n37: \n38: ```go\n39: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n40: \n41: type Reconciler struct {\n42:     client.Client\n43:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n44: }\n45: ```\n46: \n47: `SessionExpirationTimeout` SHALL be the fixed idle expiration threshold. The `Reconciler` struct SHALL embed `client.Client` for API server operations and hold a `*runtime.Scheme` for type registration.\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: SessionExpirationTimeout is 15 minutes\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** the `pkg/agentd` package is imported\n52: - **WHEN** `SessionExpirationTimeout` is read\n53: - **THEN** its value equals `15 * time.Minute`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Reconciler embeds client.Client\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** a `Reconciler` instance is constructed\n58: - **WHEN** the instance is used\n59: - **THEN** it can call `Get`, `Delete`, and other `client.Client` methods directly\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Get Sandbox and handle not found\n62: \n63: The `Reconcile` method SHALL retrieve the `Sandbox` object using `r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`. When the API server returns `NotFound`, the reconciler SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Sandbox no longer exists\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for namespace `\"default\"`, name `\"sandbox-abc\"`\n68: - **WHEN** `r.Get` returns `errors.IsNotFound(err)`\n69: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: API server error on Get\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a valid Sandbox\n74: - **WHEN** `r.Get` returns a non-NotFound error (e.g., connection refused)\n75: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Idle detection via annotation\n78: \n79: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the Sandbox metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without delete action or requeue.\n80: \n81: The constant `LastActivityAnnotationKey` SHALL be defined in `pkg/workloadmanager` with value `\"last-activity-time\"`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Annotation is missing\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with no `last-activity-time` annotation\n86: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n87: - **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` and the Sandbox is not deleted\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Annotation is empty string\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time: \"\"`\n92: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n93: - **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` and the Sandbox is not deleted\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Timestamp parsing\n96: \n97: When the `last-activity-time` annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err)`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"2026-04-10T10:00:00Z\"`\n102: - **WHEN** `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, ...)` is called\n103: - **THEN** parsing succeeds and returns the corresponding `time.Time` value\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp format\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"not-a-timestamp\"`\n108: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n109: - **THEN** the reconciler returns `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)` where `err` is the parse error\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Partial RFC3339 timestamp\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is `\"2026-04-10\"`\n114: - **WHEN** `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, ...)` is called\n115: - **THEN** parsing fails and reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold and delete\n118: \n119: The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL call `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)` to remove the Sandbox resource.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Sandbox idle beyond 15 minutes\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:16:00Z`\n124: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n125: - **THEN** `expirationTime` is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`, `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is true, and `r.Delete` is called\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Sandbox not yet expired\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:05:00Z`\n130: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n131: - **THEN** `expirationTime` is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`, `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is false, and no delete occurs\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Exactly at expiration boundary\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to `2026-04-10T10:00:00Z` and current time is `2026-04-10T10:15:00Z`\n136: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n137: - **THEN** `time.Now().After(expirationTime)` is false (equal, not after), and result is `RequeueAfter` with a small positive duration or zero\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Requeue until expiration\n140: \n141: When the Sandbox is not yet expired, the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil)` to schedule the next reconciliation at the exact expiration time.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: RequeueAfter is positive duration\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** `expirationTime` is 10 minutes in the future\n146: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n147: - **THEN** the result is `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: ~10m}` and `Requeue` is false\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: RequeueAfter approaches zero near expiration\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** `expirationTime` is 1 second in the future\n152: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n153: - **THEN** the result is `ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: ~1s}`\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n156: \n157: When `r.Delete` returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`. Other delete errors SHALL be returned as `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Sandbox already deleted by another controller\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** the LifecycleManager deleted the Sandbox between reconcile Get and Delete\n162: - **WHEN** `r.Delete` returns `errors.IsNotFound(err)`\n163: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Delete fails with transient error\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on Delete\n168: - **WHEN** `r.Delete` is called\n169: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, err)` to trigger retry\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Successful delete result\n172: \n173: When `r.Delete` succeeds (returns nil error), the system SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Delete succeeds\n176: \n177: - **GIVEN** the Sandbox exists and is expired\n178: - **WHEN** `r.Delete` returns nil\n179: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: SetupWithManager\n182: \n183: The system SHALL provide a `SetupWithManager` method on `Reconciler` that registers the controller with the manager:\n184: \n185: ```go\n186: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n187:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n188:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n189:         Complete(r)\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Controller is registered\n194: \n195: - **GIVEN** a valid `ctrl.Manager`\n196: - **WHEN** `r.SetupWithManager(mgr)` is called\n197: - **THEN** the function returns `nil` and the controller is registered to watch Sandbox resources\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: Binary entry point — Scheme registration\n200: \n201: The `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL construct a scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`:\n202: \n203: ```go\n204: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n205: \n206: func init() {\n207:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n208:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n209: }\n210: ```\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Scheme contains core and Sandbox types\n213: \n214: - **GIVEN** the `init` function has run\n215: - **WHEN** `schemeBuilder` is inspected\n216: - **THEN** it recognizes both core `v1.Pod` and `sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox` types\n217: \n218: ### Requirement: Binary entry point — Manager configuration\n219: \n220: The binary SHALL construct a controller-runtime Manager with the following options:\n221: \n222: ```go\n223: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n224:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n225:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n226:     HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\",\n227: })\n228: ```\n229: \n230: Metrics server SHALL be disabled (`BindAddress: \"0\"`). Health probe server SHALL be disabled (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Manager starts without metrics or health endpoints\n233: \n234: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig is available\n235: - **WHEN** `ctrl.NewManager` is called with the specified options\n236: - **THEN** no metrics or health probe HTTP servers are started\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Invalid kubeconfig fails fast\n239: \n240: - **GIVEN** no valid kubeconfig is available\n241: - **WHEN** `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` is called\n242: - **THEN** the process exits with a non-zero status\n243: \n244: ### Requirement: Binary entry point — Controller registration and startup\n245: \n246: The binary SHALL register the reconciler and start the manager:\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: if err := (&agentd.Reconciler{\n250:     Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n251:     Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n252: }).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n253:     // exit with error\n254: }\n255: \n256: if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n257:     // exit with error\n258: }\n259: ```\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Signal-driven graceful shutdown\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** the manager is running\n264: - **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n265: - **THEN** `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()` triggers graceful shutdown and `mgr.Start` returns\n266: \n267: ### Requirement: Package layout\n268: \n269: The system SHALL organize code as follows:\n270: \n271: ```\n272: cmd/agentd/\n273: └── main.go              — Binary entry point\n274: pkg/agentd/\n275: ├── reconciler.go        — Reconciler struct, Reconcile, SetupWithManager\n276: ├── reconciler_test.go   — Unit tests\n277: └── const.go             — SessionExpirationTimeout constant\n278: ```\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Package compiles\n281: \n282: - **GIVEN** all files are in place\n283: - **WHEN** `go build ./cmd/agentd/` is run\n284: - **THEN** the build succeeds and produces an `agentd` binary\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: Package tests pass\n287: \n288: - **GIVEN** all test cases are implemented\n289: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` is run\n290: - **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n291: \n292: ### Requirement: Reconcile algorithm completeness\n293: \n294: The `Reconcile` method SHALL implement the following algorithm exactly:\n295: \n296: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`\n297: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n298: 3. If other get error → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n299: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`\n300: 5. If `!exists || lastActivityStr == \"\"` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n301: 6. `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n302: 7. If parse error → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n303: 8. `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n304: 9. If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n305:    - `err := r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`\n306:    - If err and not `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n307:    - `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n308: 10. Else → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: Full happy path — expired sandbox deleted\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time` set to 20 minutes ago\n313: - **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n314: - **THEN** steps 1-9 execute, `Delete` is called, and `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` is returned\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: Full happy path — not yet expired requeues\n317: \n318: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox with `last-activity-time` set to 5 minutes ago\n319: - **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n320: - **THEN** steps 1-8 and 10 execute, returning `RequeueAfter: ~10m`\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: Missing annotation short-circuits\n323: \n324: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox without `last-activity-time`\n325: - **WHEN** `Reconcile` is called\n326: - **THEN** steps 1-5 execute, returning `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` at step 5\n327: \n328: ### Requirement: Code quality gates\n329: \n330: The codebase SHALL pass the following checks after implementation:\n331: \n332: - `go vet ./pkg/agentd/... ./cmd/agentd/...` produces no warnings\n333: - `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` passes all tests\n334: - `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: go vet clean\n337: \n338: - **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n339: - **WHEN** `go vet ./pkg/agentd/... ./cmd/agentd/...` is run\n340: - **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: All tests pass\n343: \n344: - **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n345: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/agentd/...` is run\n346: - **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: No unused dependencies\n349: \n350: - **GIVEN** AR-018 is implemented\n351: - **WHEN** `go mod tidy` is run\n352: - **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` are unchanged\n\n(End of file - total 352 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/agentd`, `cmd/agentd`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `idle-cleanup/spec.md`, `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler watches Sandbox CR\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API group `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`. The reconciler SHALL be triggered on Sandbox create and update events via `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).Complete(r)`.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox creation triggers reconcile\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** a new `Sandbox` object is created in the cluster\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object's namespace and name","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847761602,"end":1775847761610}}}}
